1: # `database/<table>.json` — table schema
2: 
3: One JSON file per table, keyed by the file **basename** (`database/articles.json` → table `articles`); the table name is NOT stored inside the JSON `sdk/org/libs/core/src/db/schema.ts:93-107`. A schema file is a **declarative table definition**, not seed data — it is compiled into a real SQLite `CREATE TABLE` statement at boot `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/store.ts#schemaToCreateTableSql`. Written by the authoring globals `writeTableSchema(name, schema)` (catalog templates) and `writeProjectTable(name, schema)` (the live project), both gated by the `db:schema` capability `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/authoring/globals.ts:172-183` `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/authoring/globals.ts:349-365`. Table names are snake_case (`^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$`), used verbatim in `CREATE TABLE <name>` `sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/authoring/globals.ts#AppAuthoringGlobals`.
4: 
5: ## Format
6: 
7: ```json
8: {
9:   "title": "Articles",
10:   "description": "A synthesized, personalized news article shown in the user's feed.",
11:   "columns": {
12:     "id":        { "type": "string",  "description": "unique id", "primaryKey": true, "generated": "uuid" },
13:     "title":     { "type": "string",  "description": "headline shown in the feed", "required": true },
14:     "score":     { "type": "number",  "description": "personalization relevance rank; higher = surfaced first", "default": 0 },
15:     "read":      { "type": "boolean", "description": "whether the user has opened it", "default": false },
16:     "tags":      { "type": "json",    "description": "topic tag strings — feed filtering" },
17:     "createdAt": { "type": "date",    "description": "when the article entered the feed", "generated": "now" }
18:   },
19:   "relations": {
20:     "citations": { "hasMany": "citations", "via": "articleId", "description": "the raw items this article was synthesized from" }
21:   }
22: }
23: ```
24: 
25: Adapted from `store/projects/blog/database/articles.json` (a real catalog template).
26: 
27: ## Top-level fields
28: 
29: - **`title`** — a display title for the table `sdk/org/libs/core/src/db/schema.ts#TableSchema`.
30: - **`description`** — required and fail-loud; a missing/blank one throws `<table>: table is missing required "description"` `sdk/org/libs/core/src/db/validate.ts#validateTableSchema`.
